timelineItems.desc: Columbus Crew SC look to continue their push for first place in the Eastern Conference while the Portland Timbers try to hold on to their playoff spot as they meet for their first time in 2015 at Mapre Stadium
timelineItems.title: KICKOFF: Columbus Crew SC vs. Portland Timbers | September 26, 2015

timelineItems.name: Jessica Lawrence
timelineItems.text: At my first away @TimbersFC game!! Green in the middle of a field of yellow! #RCTID @MLS http://t.co/m4O7zXIRGg

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 1': The moment we've all been waiting for... kickoff! #CrewSC is underway vs. @TimbersFC at @MAPFREStadium. #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: Portland Timbers
timelineItems.text: 18' Cross from the right side by CLB narrowly misses the head of Kamara running through the area. Still scoreless in #CLBvPOR. #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Massive Report
timelineItems.text: Full time. #CrewSC fall to #PTFC 2-1.

timelineItems.name: Chris Rifer
timelineItems.text: That's a massive win. Credit to the Timbers for picking up the pieces from last week. #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: And it's over. #CrewSC fall to #PTFC 2-1 in front of a massive crowd. Playoffs remain unclinched, missed chance to get #1 Eastern seed

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: FT: #CrewSC vs. Portland Timbers 1-2 http://t.co/6yTayI775W

timelineItems.name: Amy Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: That said, not a great performance for #CrewSC tonight. Leaving points on the field at home not good just before the playoffs.

timelineItems.name: Major League Soccer
timelineItems.text: FT: Adi's brace hands @TimbersFC a huge road win in Columbus: http://t.co/nUkZQIuPPp #CLBvPOR http://t.co/lVat0LK4Yn

timelineItems.name: Jamie Goldberg
timelineItems.text: That's it. Timbers beat Crew 2-1. Great performance and response from the Timbers, especially after last week's loss to NYRB #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Kip Kesgard
timelineItems.text: 20' - Powell makes great run on right but it's blocked out for throw. Timbers really holding their own early, hope this continues. #rctid

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: 21' You don't see that often. Nice build-up, but the pass takes a poor hop from Waylon Francis and it dribbles out of play. #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: Carlos D. Mojica
timelineItems.text: Nice passing sequence by #CrewSC in the offensive half, but the last pass was just a bit too hard. #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: Andrew Todd-Smith
timelineItems.text: Witnessing wonderful footwork by Adi with a behind-the-back service tap to Nagbe in MF. Good closing speed, #CrewSC no slouch either though.

timelineItems.text: 23': Trapp finds Meram going forward, and he looks for Francis on the left wing, but puts a little too much on it. #CrewSC #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.text: Ref doing a lot of talking to try and keep players calm, but I'm not sure its working. Expect cards soon. #CrewSC #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: Centro Deportivo
timelineItems.text: 27' KAMARA! The forward gets his head on a cross, but it goes right over the crossbar. Nearly opened up the score. #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.text: Kamara very nearly got one there. Connected on a Francis cross, but it was high. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Portland Timbers
timelineItems.text: 28' GOOOOOOAAAAAALLLLLL AAAAADDDDDDIIIIII ! #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 28': Portland goal. Darlington Nagbe tips it through to Fanendo Adi, who slams it home on the half-volley. #CrewSC #CLBvPOR 0-1

timelineItems.text: Nagbe is straight killing it. #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: That's now 11 straight games without a shutout for the #CrewSC defense.

timelineItems.name: Portland Timbers
timelineItems.text: Nagbe with a cheeky pass into the box between two defenders and Adi one-times his shot from the left side by Clark for the 1-0 lead. #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Chris Rifer
timelineItems.text: That was so, so filthy from Nagbe. Great finish from Adi, too. But goodness gracious, Darlington. #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Andy Edwards
timelineItems.text: That's the kind of killer pass you want to see from Darlington Nagbe every week. Just split 3 defenders with a chipped pass. Goal. #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC

timelineItems.text: 48' Powell, Villafana and Ridgewell all makes plays to help end a threat by Crew SC. #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Terri Botsko
timelineItems.text: #CrewSC @CapitalLaw Says Go Crew! http://t.co/D9njPblYus

timelineItems.name: Kip Kesgard
timelineItems.text: 3' - Columbus applies pressure with Kamara, forces Powell into awkward clearance attempt, but Timbers finally relieve pressure. #rctid

timelineItems.name: Carlos D. Mojica
timelineItems.text: A lot of intensity in the early minutes of this match. #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 50': Portland goal. Adi's second comes on a slot from Wallace. #CrewSC #CLBvPOR 1-2

timelineItems.name: Chris Rifer
timelineItems.text: Adi: ✌️ #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Massive Report
timelineItems.text: 50’ Adi steers home the Wallace centering cross as #PTFC attacks at pace and #CrewSC trails 2-1.

timelineItems.name: Portland Timbers
timelineItems.text: 50' GOOOAAAAAALLLL! Adi with this second goal of the night gives the Timbers a 2-1 lead! #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Jamie Goldberg
timelineItems.text: 50' - GOAL! Adi taps in the ball off a cross from Wallace. Adi always seems to score in twos... Timbers lead 2-1 #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Kip Kesgard
timelineItems.text: 50' Adi gets 2nd goal of game - 12th in 2015 season - as Wallace feeds up left side. Adi pushes it into goal for Timbers 2 to 1 lead. #rctid

timelineItems.name: Jamie Goldberg
timelineItems.text: Adi has set the MLS Timbers single season record for goals scored with 12 #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Chris Rifer
timelineItems.text: That assist, BTW, was vintage Wallace. All hard work and smarts. No grace whatsoever. #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Portland Timbers
timelineItems.text: Great attack down the left side and Wallace serves up a nice ball into the box for Adi, who steers a shot inside the far post. #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Sven
timelineItems.text: That Adi goal was really great. On another note, Villafaña has lost his steam in the 2nd half of this season. Not the player he was. #rctid

timelineItems.name: Kip Kesgard
timelineItems.text: 52' Timbers holding ball but foul gives Crew chance to attack. They seem to be pressing here but Timbers not rattled. #rctid

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 53': Finlay works into the box, but his driven cross is blocked. #CrewSC #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: Kip Kesgard
timelineItems.text: 54' - Timbers get counter with Adi but Wahl holding him by shirt. Petrescu makes foul call to give Timbers restart. #rctid

timelineItems.name: Shaina Page
timelineItems.text: Ok, seriously. Can we please keep @rodwallace22 in the Starting XI moving forward! That guy is doing work tonight! #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Carlos D. Mojica
timelineItems.text: Ten minutes into the second half and #CrewSC has mostly been on the backfoot. #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: Bob O'Shaughnessy
timelineItems.text: #TIFOSWEAT Killing it. #CrewSC http://t.co/JAF6gunlWH

timelineItems.name: Kip Kesgard
timelineItems.text: 56' - Timbers earn CK off great Nagbe run. Crew D doesn't have answer at this point. #rctid

timelineItems.name: Amy Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: #CrewSC has been on the back foot since that goal. Need to get it together before we have another FC Dallas game on our hands.

timelineItems.name: Kip Kesgard
timelineItems.text: 57' Valeri & Tchani are exchanging words & shoves as Timbers move forward. Nagbe run gives PDX forward run, Valeri earns another CK. #rctid

timelineItems.name: Kip Kesgard
timelineItems.text: 56' - CK finds Borchers but header is pushed out for JJ. Cross cleared by Kamara for 2nd CK. Effort good but foul stops run. #rctid

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 59': Meram's cross is through everyone in the box. An excellent ball! #CrewSC #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: Five minutes in. Extra seating on the stage at the north end looks packed. Rest of the stands filling in. #CrewSC #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: Kip Kesgard
timelineItems.text: 60' Great cross from left nearly finds Finlay but it's too high. Kwarasey late to react to CK & deflection but he made play. #rctid

timelineItems.name: Dan Brunell
timelineItems.text: Did the entire roster hit the gym this week? Lot more physical. #rctid

timelineItems.name: Kip Kesgard
timelineItems.text: 61' Crew gets CK off Powell clearance of cross. Looked like it should be throw, but PDX clears out restart easily. #rctid

timelineItems.name: Kip Kesgard
timelineItems.text: 62' Powell with great move to keep Kamara away from pass. Francis tries to keep ball but Nagbe makes good run to stop threat. #rctid

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: Gregg Berhalter is making moves. Mohammed Saeid and Cedrick Mabwati about to come in. #CrewSC

timelineItems.desc: Offside, Columbus Crew SC. Kei Kamara tries a through ball, but Ethan Finlay is caught offside.
timelineItems.title: CALLED BACK: Ethan Finlay is caught offside on Kamara's equalizer

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 62': Meram takes a look from outside the box with his right. Not enough on it. #CrewSC #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: Kip Kesgard
timelineItems.text: 63' - Timbers get good run forward but Adi called for foul. Fanendo has worked hard as Crew cross for Finlay is long. #rctid

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: 64' Ethan FInlay chests the ball into the net. The scoreboard proclaims "GOAL." It's waved off. #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: Portland Timbers
timelineItems.text: 64' CLB is called offside, which calls back a goal scoring play. Timbers still lead, 2-1. #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Chris Rifer
timelineItems.text: The Timbers' pressure has been really variable tonight. Looks to have Columbus out of sorts through midfield. #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Bob O'Shaughnessy
timelineItems.text: Nice to be in a box to watch the replay. AR got the call right. Finlay was off on Kamara’s touch. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Amy Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: Seems like every time I look at the screen - Kamara is on the ground. #POR hacking away with impunity at him tonight. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Meram's header juuuuuust wide. Kicks the back of the net in frustration after missing that. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 67': Meram sneaks around Adi and gets up for the header, but it's just wide! #CrewSC #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Kamara down in the box. Limping hard now. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Kip Kesgard
timelineItems.text: 68' Crew make great run with Cedrick out wide courtesy of Kamara work, but Kwarasey makes good catch to stop threat. #rctid

timelineItems.name: Chris Rifer
timelineItems.text: Columbus's tempo has gone up dramatically since the sub. Important spell for PTFC. #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Centro Deportivo
timelineItems.text: 6' Afful attempts a cross but is deemed to be offside. #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 70': Great defending by Afful sparks an attack for #CrewSC. He gets on the end of the play serving a ball into the box. #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: Andrew Todd-Smith
timelineItems.text: Meram commits near turnover, but Francis and Pipa there to wrest back possession on errant volley. Clustering of #CrewSC could be dangerous.

timelineItems.name: Kip Kesgard
timelineItems.text: 71' - Crew try to make throw in but Petrescu stops. Ball knocked out for GK for PDX but Higuain made great run to make play close. #rctid

timelineItems.name: Amy Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: Steve Clark is fearless at times. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 72': Steve Clark comes up big again for #CrewSC. He smothers a free kick by Valeri. #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: Portland Timbers
timelineItems.text: This in from #StatMan: @fanendo has more two-goal performances than any other #MLS player over the last two seasons. He has 8. #RCTID

timelineItems.name: WrongSideOfThePond
timelineItems.text: As things have progressed, #PTFC pressing less & less. Resulting drop in #CrewSC midfield turnovers has dampened Portland's attack. #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: Joe Salvati
timelineItems.text: Timbers are so much more dangerous when Nagbe runs at people. #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Kip Kesgard
timelineItems.text: 72' - Wahl fouls Adi for Timbers FK at center pitch 30 yrds out. Valeri restart dropped to Wallace but Clark falls on ball to stop. #rctid

timelineItems.name: Rick Thomas
timelineItems.text: What's it gonna be Columbus? You're at home. #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: Massive317
timelineItems.text: The effort is still there, but feels like #CrewSC are imploding on themselves...

timelineItems.name: Jamie Goldberg
timelineItems.text: Francis just shoved Valeri. #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Kip Kesgard
timelineItems.text: 75' - Francis shoved Valeri to give him room to take restart. Timbers really showing feisty play here all night. #rctid

timelineItems.name: Portland Timbers
timelineItems.text: 78' Tough foul by Powell sets up a dangerous FK opportunity at the left side of the area. #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: Tonight's crowd at @MAPFREStadium is a record sellout of 22,719 people. It's the largest since 2004. Thank you, #CrewSC supporters! #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: Portland Timbers
timelineItems.text: 7' Powell holds strong to shield off CLB's Francis in the corner. Still scoreless early. #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Kip Kesgard
timelineItems.text: 80' Higuain FK is clear to Kwarasey & cleared. Crew circling but JJ makes good clearance to help stem tide. #rctid

timelineItems.name: Portland Timbers
timelineItems.text: Timbers doing well to deal with the pressure by Crew SC, staying compact. Timbers still lead 2-1 with 10 minutes to play. #RCTID

timelineItems.desc: Attempt saved. Diego Chara (Portland Timbers) right footed shot from the right side of the box is saved in the bottom left corner.
timelineItems.title: SAVE: Steve Clark makes an acrobatic stop on Chara's blast

timelineItems.name: Chris Rifer
timelineItems.text: Little thing, but that defensive sequence from Wallace was outstanding. Great shift right there. #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Larry W. Johnson
timelineItems.text: This is where a bad defense hurts - when opponent is still pressing late and you're down a goal. #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: Amy Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: Not feeling like #CrewSC has an equalizer in them tonight. I'd love to be proven wrong though.

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Columbus now out of subs, so have to hope Kamara doesn't take another hit. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 80': Trapp's through ball to Afful is just a bit too far. Cedrick claps, encouraging Wil after the play. #CrewSC #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: Portland Timbers
timelineItems.text: 82' On the break, Chara on the receiving end of a pass in the box and forces Clark into a save. #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Sideshow Scott
timelineItems.text: aw man, I wish Chara would've buried that. #rctid

timelineItems.name: Jamie Goldberg
timelineItems.text: 82' - Chara with a great shot in the box but Clark makes the diving stop #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Jon Wong
timelineItems.text: I love it when we have @DiegoChara21 shooting! It also means that the other CDM is holding and protecting the back line #rctid

timelineItems.name: John Bava III
timelineItems.text: Jimenez on for Meram. I was kinda surprised Cedrick didn't come in for him given his comfort on the left but he's moved there now. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Amy Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: Maybe the emotion of the game, with all the legends and the 20 year celebration has just put the team out of sync. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Amy Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: God Cedrick Mabwati is fast. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Kip Kesgard
timelineItems.text: 84' - Long run for Melano is stopped by Wahl deflection for throw. Melano walking gingerly but he's fine as Cedrick makes left run. #rctid

timelineItems.name: Patrick Guldan
timelineItems.text: #CrewSC energy dropping as #PTFC in a very solid defensive shell.

timelineItems.name: Eric W
timelineItems.text: Kamara goes down in the box. Fans want a PK. No dice. #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Portland Timbers
timelineItems.text: 86' Powell with a great defensive effort 1v1 at the edge of the box, leads to a break up field by Portland. #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Eric W
timelineItems.text: Borcher vs Kamara in the box is quite the battle right now. #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: #CrewSC players are REALLY looking for PKs now. Pretty transparent.

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 87': Portland makes its final sub: George Fochive for Diego Valeri. #CrewSC #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.desc: Federico Higuain (Columbus Crew SC) is shown the yellow card for a bad foul.
timelineItems.title: YELLOW CARD: Fedrico Higuain is booked for a bad challenge

timelineItems.name: Chris Rifer
timelineItems.text: Timbers are looking gassed. Nobody supporting Valeri on that last play. Hanging on now. #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Kip Kesgard
timelineItems.text: 88' - Timbers bunkering as Higuain gets YC for hard foul on Villafana. Got elbow up in face for easy call. #rctid

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Adi visibly upset at the no call after hes taken down in the box by Trapp. #CrewSC #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: Wow. Goal-saving tackle from Wil Trapp. Took down Nagbe, who wanted a penalty. Did he deserve it? #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Matthew Doyle
timelineItems.text: That has to be a penalty. @TimbersFC 100% have a gripe. #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: beior
timelineItems.text: Why just one striker why god why #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Kip Kesgard
timelineItems.text: 90' - Timbers holding ball in their end for throw. Waiting for stoppage time number as clock winds down here. #rctid

timelineItems.name: Eric W
timelineItems.text: Nagbe finds Melano who heads to the corner to waste some time. #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Eric W
timelineItems.text: Fochive forces a turnover, Chara gets it to Melano, who chips towards Clark instead of taking it to the corner. Odd. #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: The playoffs seem inevitable, but it's looking like they will have to wait another night for #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Andrew Todd-Smith
timelineItems.text: 90'+2 #Caution issued to Fochive, likely could be argued to be red-worthy. Rough tackle on Pipa. Chances, time waning for #CrewSC. #MLS

timelineItems.name: Connor Schwepe
timelineItems.text: How did Fochive not get red? #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 90'+3': Saeid chips one into the box for Kei, but Kamara can't get his head on it. #CrewSC #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 90'+4': Kwarasey is issued a yellow card for wasting time. #CrewSC #CLBvPOR

timelineItems.name: Centro Deportivo
timelineItems.text: Another minute of added time. #CLBvPOR
